==English==

To depress or bear down with haughty, stern looks, or with arrogant speech and dogmatic assertions; to abash or disconcert by impudent or abusive words or looks; to bully; as, to browbeat witnesses<ref>Webster, 1913</ref>

===Alternative forms===
* [[brow-beat]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP|US}} {{IPA|/ˈbrɑʊ.biːt/}}, {{SAMPA|/"braU.bi:t/}}
* {{audio|en-us-browbeat.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|browbeats|browbeating|browbeat|browbeaten}}

# {{transitive}} To [[bully]] in an [[intimidating]], [[bossy]], or [[supercilious]] way.
#: ''Though the teacher '''browbeat''' all the children, they still acted out during the lesson.''

